excerpt: Rotating art exhibitions & cultural activities in a cutting-edge venue designed by Renzo Piano.
detail_description: Centro Botín is a cutting-edge venue in Santander, designed by Renzo Piano and opened in June 2017. It features rotating art exhibitions and cultural activities, with 2500 sq meters of gallery space on two floors. The modernist building also offers futuristic upper-level viewing platforms that extend over the Bahia de Santander. The ground-floor cafe has become a social hub, and the surrounding plaza is popular for various activities.
name: Centro Botín
address: Plaza Emilio Botín, P.º de Pereda, s/n, 39004 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Scenic destination featuring a historical palace with gardens, a small zoo, beaches & a lighthouse.
detail_description: Magdalena Peninsula is a historical and scenic destination featuring a palace with gardens, a small zoo, beaches, and a lighthouse. The wide boulevards of the old town offer picturesque views of fishermen along the waterfront. The verdant Magdalena Peninsula provides an opportunity to enjoy the warm sandy shore and experience the ocean. The peninsula also houses the summer residence of King Alfonso XIII and Queen Victoria Eugenia, now known as the Palace.
name: Magdalena Peninsula
address: Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Royal summer residence from the early 20th century with period decor, scenic water views & tours.
detail_description: Palacio de la Magdalena is a historic royal summer residence built in the early 20th century on the Peninsula of La Magdalena, Santander. It was constructed to serve as the official summer residence for the Spanish Royal Family and was designed by architects Javier Gonzalez de Riancho and Gonzalo Bringas. The palace, which cost 700,000 pesetas of 1912, now houses Menendez Pelayo International University and serves as a meeting and conference center.
name: Palacio de la Magdalena
address: Av. de la Magdalena, 1, 39005 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Mercado de la Esperanza is a vibrant and bustling market located in the heart of the city. Unlike other markets, it has retained its traditional charm and is not converted into a gastronomic hub. The building itself is an architectural gem, dating back to 1904 and showcasing turn-of-the-century iron architecture. The market offers a wide array of fresh seafood, local produce such as cheeses, sobaos, and quesadas, as well as traditional Spanish delicacies.
name: Mercado de la Esperanza
address: Pl. de la Esperanza, s/n, 39002 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Modern museum with artifacts from prehistoric times to the Middle Age, plus interactive exhibits.
detail_description: The Museum of Prehistory and Archaeology of Cantabria (MUPAC) is a modern museum that showcases artifacts from prehistoric times to the Middle Ages. It houses material remains from renowned archaeological sites such as La Garma, El Castillo, and Altamira, along with stone tools and portable art. Located on the ground floor of Mercado del Este, it also features interactive exhibits.
name: Museum of Prehistory and Archaeology of Cantabria
address: C. Bailén, s/n, 39004 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Santander is the capital city of the Cantabria region on Spain’s north coast. The Palacio de la Magdalena, once the royal summer residence, lies at the mouth of the Bay of Santander on the rocky La Magdalena Peninsula. West, the city center is home to the Catedral de Santander, with its octagonal cupola and Gothic cloister. Nearby, the Paseo de Pereda promenade runs along one side of the Jardines de Pereda gardens.
detail_description: Santander, the capital city of Cantabria in northern Spain, is known for its stunning landmarks and rich history. The Palacio de la Magdalena, a former royal summer residence located on the La Magdalena Peninsula, offers breathtaking views of the Bay of Santander.
name: Santander
address: Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: This bustling neoclassical Herrerian square was inaugurated in 1950 after the fire of 1941.
detail_description: Plaza Porticada, also known as Plaza Velarde, is a lively neoclassical square located in the heart of Santander. It offers stunning views of the portico-lined plaza and the city's expansive bay. Many major attractions such as the Gothic cathedral, Museum of Prehistory and Archaeology, Centro Botin, Paseo de Pereda promenade, and Banco Santander building are just a few minutes' walk away.
name: Plaza Porticada
address: Pl. Porticada, S/n, 39003 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: El Sardinero is located near the Peninsula de la Magdalena and is known as Santander's most extensive and well-liked beach. It is divided into two parts by a rocky headland, offering visitors a picturesque coastal setting to enjoy.
name: El Sardinero
address: 39005 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: El Sardinero in Santander is a popular seafront area with magnificent beaches like Camello, La Concha, and the Sardinero beaches. These golden sandy stretches offer opportunities for sunbathing, surfing, and enjoying games like palas. Visitors can also relax at El Piquio gardens or indulge in delicious ice cream from local vendors. The beach is divided by a beautiful lookout point and offers stunning views of the Atlantic.
name: El Sardinero
address: 39005 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Lighthouse built in 1839 within a park, popular for sunset views & walks along the cliffs & beaches.
detail_description: The Centro de Arte Faro Cabo Mayor, also known as the Cabo Mayor Lighthouse, is a historic lighthouse built in 1839 located within a park in Santander. It offers stunning sunset views and opportunities for walks along the cliffs and beaches. Situated on a cliff, it provides an ideal vantage point to admire the rugged coastline and the vast Atlantic Ocean.
name: Centro de Arte Faro Cabo Mayor
address: Av. del Faro, 39012 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Exhibits about local maritime heritage, whale skeletons, an aquarium & a restaurant with bay views.
detail_description: Situated on the waterfront overlooking the Bay of Santander, Museo Marítimo del Cantábrico is a maritime museum that offers a fascinating insight into the nautical history of Santander. The museum showcases traditional Spanish boats, ship-building techniques, cartography collections, and marine biology displays. Visitors can also explore exhibits about local fishing traditions and industry. Additionally, the museum houses an aquarium featuring marine life from the bay and ocean.
name: Museo Marítimo del Cantábrico
address: Av. de Severiano Ballesteros, s/n, 39004 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Set in a cove, this busy beach with fine sand is accessed by a steep set of stairs.
detail_description: Playa de Mataleñas is a stunning cove beach with fine sand and turquoise waters, nestled between cliffs near Santander. Accessible via steep stairs, it offers a peaceful haven away from the bustling Playa Sardinero. The area also features attractions like the Ethnography Museum and beautiful gardens around Centro Botin. Additionally, the Sercotel Palacio del Mar Hotel offers event spaces including the spacious Matalenas room equipped with modern amenities for meetings or weddings.
name: Playa de Mataleñas
address: 39012 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Developed beach with snack bars & lounger rentals, plus strong breezes that create surf breaks.
detail_description: Primera Playa del Sardinero is a well-developed beach in Santander, Cantabria, Spain. It offers snack bars and loungers for rent, and its strong breezes create surf breaks. The area is known for its stunning coastline and pristine beaches like Playa de la Magdalena. Visitors can soak up the sun or indulge in water sports at this iconic tourist destination.
name: Primera Playa del Sardinero
address: Plaza de Italia, Av. Castañeda, 5, 39005 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Cabo Mayor is a must-visit spot on the northern Iberian coast, offering magnificent views of the Atlantic Ocean. The power of the crashing waves against the rocks creates a mesmerizing sight, and visitors can gaze out into the vast sea. It's recommended to visit Cabo Mayor Lighthouse for its stunning panoramic views. Accessible from the road, it offers an awesome experience for travelers.
name: Cabo Mayor
address: Spain

detail_description: Jardines de Piquio is a romantic park located in the El Sardinero district of Santander, Spain. It offers a refreshing escape with its tamarind trees and stunning views of Ensenada del Sardinero and Cabo Menor, as well as the visible Magdalena Peninsula to the south.
name: Jardines de Piquío
address: Av. Castañeda, 5, 39005 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Vibrant promenade along Santander Bay lined with historical buildings & monuments.
detail_description: P.º de Pereda is a lively promenade along Santander Bay, featuring historical buildings, monuments, and the beautiful Pereda Gardens. It separates the coastal strip from the historic quarter of Santander and offers stunning views of the bay. The area is rich in attractions such as the seaport, marina, pier, Palacete del Embarcadero, Cathedral, City Hall, Plaza Porticada and Santander Bank.
name: P.º de Pereda
address: 39004 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Puertochico in Santander is known for its non-foodie festivals that incorporate a culinary aspect. One of the notable events is the Dia del Carmen celebration, featuring a large open-air fresh sardine BBQ. This festival offers visitors the opportunity to indulge in delicious seafood while enjoying the vibrant atmosphere and cultural festivities.
name: Puertochico
address: 39003 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Playa de los Bikinis is a popular beach in Santander, known for its family-friendly atmosphere and calm waters. It is located near the Magdalena Palace and can be reached through a relaxing coastal walk from the city center. The beach got its name from foreign exchange students who introduced the bikini to Santander in the 1960s.
name: Playa de los Bikinis
address: Spain

excerpt: Grand, historic casino with table games, video poker, sports betting & a restaurant.
detail_description: Gran Casino del Sardinero is a historic casino offering table games, video poker, sports betting, and a restaurant. It is located in a beautiful natural space that includes the Peninsula of La Magdalena, home to sea lions and penguins. The casino's architecture evokes the Belle Epoque era and it is situated near the marina with yachts in Puertochico.
name: Gran Casino del Sardinero
address: Plaza de Italia, s/n, 39005 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Green space featuring paths amid reedy marshland lakes with bird life, plus a cafe & a playground.
detail_description: Parque Atlántico de Las Llamas is a vast and picturesque park located in the heart of the city. It features verdant spaces with pathways, reedy marshland lakes teeming with diverse bird species, fish, turtles and dragonflies. The park has several playgrounds for children between three to ten years old, although some may find them unremarkable. Visitors can enjoy a leisurely stroll on sunny days while taking in the lovely scenery.
name: Parque Atlántico de Las Llamas
address: Av. de la Constitución, 52A, 39005 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Large cathedral consisting of 2 churches with Gothic design elements & ancient statuary.
detail_description: The Catedral de Santander is a stunning Gothic cathedral located in the heart of Santander, Spain. It consists of two churches with ancient statuary and Gothic design elements. The city's historic quarter also offers beautiful churches and vibrant plazas, while nature lovers can explore the breathtaking landscapes of Cantabria and the nearby Picos de Europa National Park for outdoor activities.
name: Catedral de Santander
address: Plaza Obispo José Eguino y Trecu, 1, 39002 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Mercado del Este, also known as Eastern Market or Plaza del Este, is a historic and culturally significant destination in Santander. The market hosts a variety of shops and bars, offering visitors the chance to sample local pintxos and cheeses. Additionally, the ground floor is home to the Museum of Prehistory and Archaeology of Cantabria (MUPAC), which showcases archaeological finds from renowned sites like La Garma and Altamira.
name: Mercado del Este
address: C. Hernán Cortés, 4, 39003 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Playa de la Magdalena is a stunning beach located in Santander, Cantabria, Spain. It is known for its pristine coastline and offers the perfect setting for sunbathing and water sports. The area also features architectural wonders such as the majestic Palacio de la Magdalena, set against the backdrop of the sea. Families with children can enjoy the nearby playground while young people often prefer Playa de Bikini.
name: Playa de la Magdalena
address: Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Paseo Marítimo de Santander is a picturesque waterside promenade that offers a delightful stroll along the bay. Along the way, visitors can admire the old crane and the Palacete del Embarcadero, which houses a captivating museum. The promenade also features beautifully sculpted Raqueros figures by Jose Cobo Calderon, paying homage to children who used to dive into the bay for coins.
name: Paseo Marítimo de Santander
address: P.º de Pereda, 27, 39004 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: This small and stunning beach is surrounded by a beautiful green park and a coastline. The beach is the cleanest that anyone has ever been to, making it a must-visit spot for anyone looking for peace and quiet.
name: Playa de Los Molinucos
address: 39012 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: This observation deck at the top of the funicular offers sweeping views of the city & the bay.
detail_description: Mirador Rio de la Pila is an observation deck located at the top of a funicular, providing stunning panoramic views of the city and the bay. Visitors can stroll along the promenade, passing beneath wisteria-hung archways that line the waterfront and continue towards Parque de Matalenas and the lighthouse mirador of Cabo Mayor before returning to Sardinero.
name: Mirador Rio de la Pila
address: C. Río de la Pila, S/N, 39001 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Barrio Pesquero is a charming fishing district located beyond the old town of Santander. It surrounds the marina and is home to the fish market and a collection of restaurants. While it's known for serving some of the city's finest seafood, visitors should plan their visit earlier in the day as many establishments close early. The neighborhood offers a peaceful atmosphere with its picturesque streets and plazas, making it an ideal place for a leisurely stroll.
name: Barrio Pesquero
address: 39009 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Popular for swimming & sunbathing, this sandy strip has views of the rugged Magdalena Peninsula.
detail_description: Playa Del Camello, located near the Magdalena Peninsula, is a family-friendly beach known for its natural beauty and urban amenities. The pristine sands and calm waters make it perfect for swimming and sunbathing. Equipped with facilities like showers, lifeguards, and beach bars, visitors can enjoy a comfortable experience. The beach also features a unique rock formation resembling a camel, adding to its charm.
name: Playa Del Camello
address: Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Parque de Mataleñas is a sprawling 60-acre park located in Santander, Spain, nestled between the beaches of El Sardinero and Matalenas. The park offers woodland trails, meadows, a large lake, and even native deer. Visitors can also enjoy a small zoo and an affordable golf course within the park. Additionally, the Real Palacio de La Magdalena sits at the tip of a peninsula within the park grounds and offers stunning sea views.
name: Parque de Mataleñas
address: Av. del Faro, 12, 39012 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: 200-meter sandy beach with calm water for swimming & water sports, plus public showers.
detail_description: Playa Los Peligros is a 200-meter sandy beach with calm waters, making it perfect for swimming and water sports. It features public showers for convenience. The beach can be easily accessed from the Palacio de Festivales building in Puerto Chico harbor or by taking a relaxing coastal walk from the city center. Despite its name, which means 'danger' in Spanish, Playa Los Peligros is family-friendly and suitable for everyone to enjoy together.
name: Playa Los Peligros
address: Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Located in Santander, the Museo de Arte Moderno y Contemporáneo de Santander y Cantabria (MAS) has been evolving since its establishment in 1908. It serves as a hub for the exchange of ideas and knowledge about modern and contemporary art. The museum boasts a diverse collection featuring works by both renowned artists like Miro and Goya, as well as lesser-known creators. Visitors can explore different periods of art on each floor, witnessing the transformation of artistic styles.
name: Museo de Arte Moderno y Contemporáneo de Santander y Cantabria
address: C. Rubio, 6, 39001 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Small bayfront building, dating to 1932, presenting temporary exhibitions & cultural programming.
detail_description: Palacete del Embarcadero is a small bayfront building that dates back to 1932 and hosts temporary exhibitions and cultural events. It was once the summer residence of King Alfonso XIII and Queen Victoria Eugenia. Visitors can explore the details of this historical site, then continue along Avenida Reina Victoria for views of the Maritime Museum of Cantabria. The nearby Dique de Gamazo offers a timeless experience opposite the Festival Centre.
name: Palacete del Embarcadero
address: Lugar, Calle Muelle de Calderón, 0 S N, 39003 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Plaza de Pombo is a charming square in the heart of Santander, offering a delightful setting to relax and soak up the local atmosphere. The plaza features outdoor cafes where you can enjoy watching schoolkids play near the bandstand. Surrounding the square are shops, cafes, and even a carousel for kids' entertainment. Additionally, there's an underground parking area available. Dating back to 1867, this iconic plaza has become an elegant spot for leisurely walks and social gatherings.
name: Plaza de Pombo
address: C. Hernán Cortés, 25, 39003 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Harbor-front bronze statues of 4 orphaned 'raqueros' children seated, standing & diving for coins.
detail_description: Los Raqueros is a popular attraction in Santander, featuring bronze statues of four orphaned children known as "raqueros." These life-size sculptures depict the boys seated, standing, and diving for coins along the Paseo de Pereda. The raqueros were marginalized children who survived by collecting coins thrown into the sea by passengers and crew members at the docks of Santander's bay.
name: Los Raqueros
address: P.º de Pereda, 34, 39004 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: In the heart of Santander lies the Biblioteca y casa-museo de Menéndez Pelayo, an iconic site with a rich history. This complex includes the Menéndez Pelayo Library, designed by architect Leonardo Rucabado and inaugurated in 1923, as well as the house museum where Marcelino Menéndez Pelayo, a prominent scholar and intellectual figure in Spanish humanistic field, lived and passed away.
name: Casa-Museo de Menéndez Pelayo
address: C. Rubio, 7, 39001 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Av de la Reina Victoria offers stunning views of Santander Bay and is a great spot for leisurely walks. Along the avenue, you can visit the Maritime Museum of Cantabria, which is highly recommended. After exploring the museum, make sure to head to Dique de Gamazo, also known as Duna, located across from the Festival Centre. This area provides timeless charm and breathtaking vistas of Santander Bay that are truly captivating.
name: Av de la Reina Victoria
address: Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Santander Central Hostel is a vibrant and welcoming option for budget-conscious travelers, conveniently situated opposite the bus and train stations and a short stroll from the old town center. The hostel offers complimentary breakfast and all-day tea, along with ample lockers, a guest kitchen, and a spacious chillout area. Guests praise the cleanliness of the hostel as well as its helpful staff. Its proximity to the city center makes it an ideal base for exploring Santander's attractions.
name: Santander Central Hostel
address: C. Calderón de la Barca, 4, Entresuelo C, 39002 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: MAS COMUNIDADES SANTANDER, S.L. is a property management company that has garnered positive feedback for its attentive and understanding approach towards addressing property-related issues. The company's efficient and decisive staff have been commended for their quick telephone service and clear communication. Additionally, the company manages various homes in different communities, providing top-notch services to its clients. Despite being closed for renovations, the Museum of Modern Art Santander (MAS) has generated anticipation among visitors eagerly awaiting its reopening.
name: MAS COMUNIDADES SANTANDER, S.L.
address: C. San José, 14, BAJO Pta. EI, 39003 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Monumento a Nuestra Señora de la Asunción is located in a well-configured square that provides lateral access to the Cathedral of Santander. The monument, featuring a beautiful sculpture depicting the Assumption of the Virgin, stands at the center of the square. It is said that this square was where the 'Invincible Armada' was built.
name: Monumento a Nuestra Señora de la Asunción
address: Pl. de Atarazanas, 2, 39002 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Puerto Chico Santander offers a blend of history and adventure. Take a stroll from El Casino to the old Tunel de Tetuan, an intriguing historical tunnel that provides a unique pedestrian pathway through the city. This tunnel offers a glimpse into the past, allowing visitors to envision the Pombo train, which once transported locals. It's an ideal spot for those seeking a leisurely exploration while delving into the city's heritage.
name: Puertochico
address: Pl. de Puertochico, 1, 39004 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Plaza Cañadío is a charming square located in the heart of Santander, Spain. It is known for its lively atmosphere and vibrant energy, with numerous cafes and restaurants lining the perimeter. The square is a popular gathering spot for both locals and tourists, offering a great opportunity to relax and people-watch.
name: Plaza Cañadío
address: 39003 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Ermita de la Virgen del Mar is a hermitage that honors the patron saint of Santander, la Virgen del Mar. While its origins date back to 1400, it has undergone multiple renovations due to exposure to the elements. Legend has it that the hermitage's location was mysteriously changed overnight during its construction. Situated on an islet in San Roman, this sanctuary can be reached via a bridge and offers a stunning viewpoint of the sea.
name: Ermita de la Virgen del Mar
address: C. el Somo, 60, 39012 San Román de la Llanilla, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Nestled just outside the vibrant city of Santander, Playa del Puntal is a hidden gem that promises an unforgettable beach getaway. This stunning stretch of golden sand can be reached via a delightful ferry ride, enhancing its charm and accessibility. Surrounded by picturesque sand dunes and lush greenery, it serves as a sanctuary for nature enthusiasts and birdwatchers alike. The area boasts historical landmarks such as the Punta de la Mesa Lighthouse and El Puntal Lighthouse, both steeped in maritime history.
name: El Puntal Beach
address: Calle el Puntal, 39140, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Muralla de Santander is a historical site located about 14km east of Laredo. It offers a glimpse into the city's past and its structure around the bay. The area features small, wild Playa de Sonabia nestled in a rock-lined inlet beneath high crags where rare griffon vultures circle above. Visitors can also explore the shelter of Mariana Pineda and the cathedral tower with exceptional guides who make the visit enjoyable.
name: Muralla de Santander
address: Pl. Velarde, 39001 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Ascensor Río de la Pila is a short funicular that covers a 50-meter route with four stops, connecting the upper and lower parts of Santander. It's not specifically for tourists, but it offers impressive views of the bay as it ascends and descends. The funicular is free to use and stops at different levels corresponding to different streets.
name: Ascensor Río de la Pila
address: C. Río de la Pila, 36, 39001 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Refugio Antiaereo Santander is a well-preserved shelter from the Spanish Civil War, offering guided tours with informative explanations about its historical significance. The site provides insight into the wartime experiences of Santander and features videos and artifacts from that era. Visitors can witness a recreated bombing to get a sense of the past. It's an intriguing piece of Santander's history, making it worth a visit to learn about the events during the Civil War in this area.
name: Refugio Antiaereo Santander
address: Pl. del Príncipe, S/N, 39003 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: La Maruca Beach is a charming coastal gem located in Santander, Cantabria, Spain. Stretching 400 meters long and 10 meters wide, this beach offers a serene atmosphere with low occupancy, making it perfect for those seeking tranquility. The picturesque landscape features rocky formations and a small estuary where boats are moored, enhancing its maritime charm. A scenic path runs alongside the beach leading to the sea, inviting visitors to explore its natural beauty further.
name: La Maruca Beach
address: 39012 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: The Palacio de Festivales de Cantabria, located in Santander, Spain, is a versatile cultural center with extensive facilities and technical infrastructure suitable for hosting various events such as congresses, meetings, and conventions. It offers a diverse artistic program throughout the year and attracts renowned national and international personalities from the arts scene. The venue is also known for hosting the International Festival of Santander (FIS), one of Spain's oldest music festivals featuring operas, ballets, and plays.
name: Palacio de Festivales de Cantabria
address: Calle de Gamazo, 39004 Santander, Cantabria, Spain

excerpt: Low peak & scenic lookout featuring dramatic bay, city & mountain panoramas.
detail_description: Peña Cabarga is a stunning mountain that serves as a beloved lookout point for the residents of Santander and nearby towns. This low peak offers breathtaking panoramic views of the dramatic bay, cityscape, and surrounding mountains. It's an ideal spot to witness mesmerizing sunsets while enjoying quality time with family or friends. The area is also home to diverse wildlife, so visitors should tread carefully.
name: Peña Cabarga
address: 39619, Cantabria, Spain

detail_description: Parque de la Marga is a delightful green space, adorned with an impressive array of trees in various shades and styles. This park offers ample room for walking, playing, and sunbathing, making it an ideal destination for relaxation and recreation. Situated centrally, it boasts a wild charm and diverse attractions that cater to every taste. It provides a serene atmosphere where visitors can enjoy the tranquility of nature while having plenty of seating options available.
name: Parque de la Marga
address: 39009 Santander, Cantabria, Spain
